info.name: Twitter-API
info.description:
# Introduction
Simple twitter API that allows you to create your own twitter posts, see own tweets, follow other users and fetch posts from you and your followed persons posts as newsfeed.

# Overview
This project uses `express.js`, `MySql`  `sequelize` to implement all the API's

# Authentication
All the endpoints of `users` are protected with `JWT` `token` validation. There is a basic level of token `blacklist` system (This will reset on each restart) for already used token (`token` that are used in for refresh token / logout ).

# Config
 This project can be configured with `.env` 

```
#APP
HOST=YOUR_HOST
APP_PORT=YOUR_PORT
LOGGER_NAME=YOUR_LOGGER_NAME
LOG_LEVEL=YOUR_LOGGER_LEVEL
NODE_ENV=YOUR_NODE_ENVIRONMENT

#Database
DB_HOSTNAME=YOUR_DATABASE_HOST
DB_PORT=YOUR_DATABASE_PORT
DB_NAME=YOUR_DATABASE_NAME
DB_USERNAME=YOUR_DATABASE_USERNAME
DB_PASSWORD=YOUR_DATABASE_PASSWORD
DB_DIALECT=mysql
DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=YOUR_DATABASE_ROOT_PASSWORD

#JWT
JWT_SECRET=YOUR_JWT_SECRET
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY=ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_IN_MINUTES
JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_IN_MINUTES

#API Rate Limiting Config
API_RATE_LIMIT_INTERVAL_IN_MIN=1
API_MAX_REQUEST_LIMIT=60
```

## Installation:

- Clone the repository: `https://github.com/akibtanjim/twitter-api.git`
- Copy `.env.example`to `.env`. Fill this with appropriate value
- For manual install please follow the below steps

  ```
      npm i
      npm run db:migrate
      npm run db:seed
      npm run test
      npm start
  ```
## Defaults:
- Admin default password is `#Admin123`
- User default password is `#User123`

This API login's a user with given `email` & `password`

password true One uppercase, one lower case alphabets, one number and one special character with min length of 8

This API will create new user with given `name`, `email` , `role` & `password`

request.headers.authorization true string

password true One uppercase, one lower case alphabets, one number and one special character with min length of 8

request.description:

request.headers.authorization true string
name required if any of email, role and password is not provided This field accepts alphabets, dot, underscore & hyphen
email required if any of name, role and password is not provided valid email address
role required if any of email, name and password is not provided admin/user
password required if any of email, role and name is not provided One uppercase, one lower case alphabets, one number and one special character with min length of 8

item.name: tweet

request.description:
This api helps authenticated user to create their own tweets by providing **descritpion** and **isPublic**.

| **Parameters** | **Required** | **Validation** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| description | true | N/A |
| isPublic | false | boolean |

response.name: (Success) Create Tweet
(Error) Create Tweet

request.description:
This api provides authenticated user with their own tweets. User can get all of their private/public/all tweets by passing **type** in query parameters. By default if no query parameter is provided it will return all the tweets.  
This api supports pagination. if **page** parameters is provided in the query parameters, it will return up to 10 items at a time along with **pagination** information.

| **Parameters** | **Required** | **Validation** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| type | false | value must be either all/public/private |
| page | false | integer |

response.name: (Success) Get Own Tweets Without Type

request.description:
This api provides authenticated user with their own as well as his follower's public tweets sorted by creation date.  
This api supports pagination. if **page** parameters is provided in the query parameters, it will return up to 10 items at a time along with **pagination** information

| **Parameters** | **Required** | **Validation** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| page | false | integer |
